Former vice president, Alhaji Abubakar Atiku, is in a closed-door meeting with former president Chief Olusegun Obasanjo, in Abeokuta. Atiku arrived at the penthouse residence of Obasanjo at the Olusegun Obasanjo Presidential Library (OOPL), Abeokuta, at about 10.00 am. The former presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) immediately went into a closed meeting with his former boss. Atiku had arrived at Ogun State, on Friday, to attend the 60th birthday of Hon. Ladi Adebutu, in Iperu Remo. He is expected to pay a courtesy visit to the Alake and Paramount Ruler of Egbaland, Oba Adedotun Gbadebo, at his palace in Abeokuta. Details later… YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Atiku in closed-door  Atiku in closed-door Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Atiku in closed-door  Atiku in closed-door ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
